e are 3 sets of rules that could apply to your journey:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/drivers-hours/eu-rules\" title=\"EU rules on drivers' hours\">EU rules</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/drivers-hours/aetr-rules\" title=\"AETR rules on drivers' hours\"><abbr title=\"European Agreement Concerning the Work of Crews Engaged in International Road Transport\">AETR</abbr> rules</a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/drivers-hours/gb-domestic-rules\" title=\"GB Domestic rules on drivers' hours\">GB Domestic rules</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The rules that apply depend on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the type of vehicle you&rsquo;re driving</li>\n  <li>which country you&rsquo;re driving in</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This guide highlights the main rules. For more detailed information you should read the following guides.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_Theme_files/Goods_vehicles_tachograph_hours_1111_3.pdf\" title=\"Download 'GV262: The rules on drivers' hours and tachographs - goods vehicles' (PDF 4.5MB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘GV262: The rules on drivers’ hours and tachographs - goods vehicles’ (PDF 4.5MB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_Theme_files/Passengercarrying_vehicles_tachograph_hours_0511.pdf\" title=\"Download 'PSV375: The rules on drivers' hours and tachographs - passenger carrying vehicles' (PDF 4.2MB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘PSV375: The rules on drivers’ hours and tachographs - passenger carrying vehicles’ (PDF 4.2MB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/drivers-hours/rules-for-employers","slug":"rules-for-employers","order":2,"title":"Rules for employers","body":"<p>As an employer, you must monitor your mobile workers&rsquo; working time and do what you can to make sure the limits aren&rsquo;t exceeded. You must record working time and keep the records for at least 2 years.</p>\n\n<p>Mobile workers are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>drivers - including employed drivers, own-account drivers, and agency drivers</li>\n  <li>members of the vehicle crew, eg a second driver on a coach</li>\n  <li>anyone else who is part of the travelling staff, eg a bus conductor, a drayman, or a security guard aboard a vehicle carrying high-value goods</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Workers who only occasionally carry out activities covered by EU drivers&rsquo; hours rules are not covered by mobile worker regulations. They need to follow <a href=\"/maximum-weekly-working-hours\" title=\"Maximum weekly working hours\">other rules</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Enforcement</h2>\n<p>The Vehicle and Operator Services Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>) enforces the regulations. If you break the rules you can be given:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>an improvement notice - setting out the changes you need to make by a certain date</li>\n  <li>a prohibition notice - this requires you to stop a dangerous activity, or to start complying with the regulations</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> takes a &lsquo;proportionate&rsquo; approach to enforcement. Formal action is usually taken only against persistent or serious offenders. </p>\n\n<p>For detailed information, download the guidance on Road Transport (Working Time) Regulations.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/+/http://www.dft.gov.uk/adobepdf/165226/workingtimeguidance.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guidance on the Road Transport (Working Time) Regulations 2005' (PDF, 211KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guidance on the Road Transport (Working Time) Regulations 2005’ (PDF, 211KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/drivers-hours/goods-vehicles","slug":"goods-vehicles","order":3,"title":"Goods vehicles","body":"<p>The rules that apply to goods vehicles depend on the weight of your vehicle, the country you&rsquo;re driving in and what you&rsquo;re using the vehicle for.</p>\n\n<h2>EU rules</h2>\n\n<p>EU rules apply if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the maximum permissible weight of your vehicle/vehicle combination is more than 3.5 tonnes</li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re driving within the EU (including the UK) </li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;re driving in a <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.companieshouse.gov.uk/about/miscellaneous/listeeaCountries.shtml\" title=\"List of European Economic Area countries\">European Economic Area (<abbr title=\"European Economic Area\">EEA</abbr>) country</a> or Switzerland</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Some vehicles are <a href=\"/drivers-hours/exemptions-from-eu-law\" title=\"Exemptions to EU rules on drivers hours\">exempt from EU rules</a> when driven in the UK.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2><abbr title=\"European Agreement Concerning the Work of Crews Engaged in International Road Transport\">AETR</abbr> rules</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"European Agreement Concerning the Work of Crews Engaged in International Road Transport\">AETR</abbr> (European Agreement Concerning the Work of Crews Engaged in International Road Transport) rules apply if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your vehicle will pass through an <a href=\"/drivers-hours/aetr-rules\" title=\"List of AETR countries\"><abbr title=\"European Agreement Concerning the Work of Crews Engaged in International Road Transport\">AETR</abbr> country</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>GB Domestic rules</h2>\n\n<p>GB Domestic rules apply if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the maximum permissible weight of your vehicle is under 3.5 tonnes</li>\n  <li>your journey is entirely in the UK</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>GB Domestic rules also apply in the UK if your vehicle is <a href=\"/drivers-hours/exemptions-from-eu-law\" title=\"Exemptions to EU rules on drivers hours\">exempt from EU rules</a>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>If you’ll be driving through a country outside of the UK, EU, <abbr title=\"European Economic Area\">EEA</abbr> or Switzerland, you should contact the UK embass