itle=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> test if it&rsquo;s a commercial vehicle or trailer used to carry explosives, or if it&rsquo;s used in the UK or abroad:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>to carry dangerous goods in bulk in a fixed tank or fixed battery of pressure vessels of over 1,000 litres capacity</li>\n  <li>for carrying dangerous goods in bulk in a container or demountable tank or battery of pressure vessels of over 3,000 litres capacity</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The test varies depending on the type of goods you want to carry.</p>\n\n<h2>How to book a test and what it costs</h2>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li><p>Fill in and send application for an <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> test.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Say on the form if the vehicle is to be tested while still carrying dangerous goods (or their residue) – <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> will make arrangements for this.</p>\n</li>\n<li><p>Include copies of insurance certificates (originals will need to be seen at the test) for fixed tanks, batteries and pressure vessels.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Application%20for%20ADR%20Road%20Vehicle%20Certification%20(ADR%20III).pdf\" title=\"Download 'Application for an ADR test' (PDF, 415KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Application for an <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> test’ (PDF, 415KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Send your application at least 10 days before you want to take the test. Send your application to the address on the form or using the contact details below.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> test booking</strong>\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#097;&#100;&#114;&#098;&#111;&#111;&#107;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#064;&#118;&#111;&#115;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#097;&#100;&#114;&#098;&#111;&#111;&#107;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#064;&#118;&#111;&#115;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a><br />\n<strong>Fax:</strong> 01792 454367</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>Vehicles and trailers need individual certification. So an articulated or drawbar combination will need 2 <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> applications, 1 for the vehicle and 1 for the trailer. You have to pay a fee for each part.</p>\n\n<h2>Fees for <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> testing and certification</h2>\n\n<p>The fees listed are in addition to the standard annual test fee.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> service</th>\n      <th>Fee</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Initial inspection</td>\n      <td>£99</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Re-inspection within 14 days</td>\n      <td>£50</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Duplicate certificate</td>\n      <td>£14</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>New type approved artic tractor certificate</td>\n      <td>£28</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>Taking your vehicle to the test</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Vehicles shouldn’t normally be loaded or uncleaned when they’re taken for the <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> test, unless special arrangements have been made with the testing station.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The exception is for vehicles loaded with UN1202 diesel, gas or heating oil where there&rsquo;s also no residue of other flammable materials in tank vapour spaces.</p>\n\n<p>If a dangerous goods vehicle is taken to the test uncleaned or purged, or is laden with dangerous goods, <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> will need to see evidence that the vehicle is accompanied by a person with an appropriate <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> driver’s licence. </p>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll need to submit form VTG15 to the testing station to show if your vehicle is carrying or has been carrying dangerous goods.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_files/066948_Certificate_For_Carriage_of_Dangerous_Goods.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Form VTG15: Certificate for vehicles which carry dangerous goods or hazardous substances' (PDF, 102KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Form VTG15: Certificate for vehicles which carry dangerous goods or hazardous substances’ (PDF, 102KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Getting a re-inspection after a failed test</h2>\n<p>If you fail the test, phone the testing station you used to arrange another inspection.</p>\n\n<h2>New goods vehicle tractor units that have &lsquo;<abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr>-type approval&rsquo;</h2>\n\n<p>If you buy a new tractor unit, ask your vehicle supplier if it has been built to an &lsquo;<abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr>-type approval&rsquo;. This mean you can get <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr>-type certification for it. The manufacturer should supply a combined Declaration of Conformity, and application form <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> IIIA, that you can then send to <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<h2>Duplicate <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> certificates</h2>\n\n<p>You can get a duplicate certificate as long as the <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> certificate is still current. You can&rsquo;t get a duplicate of an expired certificate.</p>\n\n<p>Write to <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>&rsquo;s <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> Section with the following details:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>vehicle/trailer ID</li>\n  <li>operator name and address</li>\n  <li>reason for request (eg you&rsquo;ve lost the certificate or there&rsquo;s been a change of owner/operator)</li>\n  <li>payment details</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr></strong><br />\n<abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> Section<br />\n<a href=\"&#109;&#097;&#105;&#108;&#116;&#111;:&#097;&#100;&#114;&#098;&#111;&#111;&#107;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#064;&#118;&#111;&#115;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;\">&#097;&#100;&#114;&#098;&#111;&#111;&#107;&#105;&#110;&#103;&#064;&#118;&#111;&#115;&#097;&#046;&#103;&#111;&#118;&#046;&#117;&#107;</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\n<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>\n<br /><abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses par Route\">ADR</abbr> Section\n<br />Ellipse\n<br />Padley Road\n<br />Swansea\n<br />SA1 8AN\n<br />\n</p></div></div>\n\n<h3>Change of <abbr title=\"Accord European relatif au transport international des marchandises Dangereuses pa