,"order":1,"title":"Vehicles that must take the 'annual test'","body":"<p>The annual test for lorries, trailers and buses is similar to the MOT test that cars take each year.</p>\n\n<p>The annual test is for:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>motor vehicles with a gross weight of more than 3,500 kilograms</li>\n  <li>vehicles that are built or have been adapted to form part of an articulated vehicle</li>\n  <li>semi-trailers</li>\n  <li>horseboxes with a gross weight of more than 3,500 <abbr title=\"Kilograms\">kg</abbr></li>\n  <li>&lsquo;A&rsquo; frame trailers and converter dollies manufactured on or after 1 January 1979</li>\n  <li>other trailers with an unladen weight of more than 1,020 <abbr title=\"Kilograms\">kg</abbr></li>\n  <li>all public service vehicles with more than 8 passenger seats - not including the driver&rsquo;s seat</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>About the test</h2>\n\n<p>Lorries and buses (including coaches) must be tested each year. The first test should be 12 months after the vehicle was first registered with DVLA (Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency).</p>\n\n<p>Trailers must be tested 1 year after they were first sold or supplied.</p>\n\n<p>The test can be done at a <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> Goods Vehicle Testing Station (<abbr title=\"Goods Vehicle Testing Station\">GVTS</abbr>) or a privately owned Authorised Testing Facility (<abbr title=\"Authorised Testing Facility\">ATF</abbr>). Both use <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> staff and the same test standards.</p>\n\n<h2>Before the test</h2>\n\n<p>You can get your vehicle checked by a qualified mechanic to prepare for the test.</p>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/publications/manualsandguides/vehicletestingmanualsandguides.htm\" title=\"Vehicle testing manuals and guides\">Testing manuals</a> for different vehicles are available from <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>.  Owners of horseboxes and trailers can also download a guide on how to check the roadworthiness of their vehicle. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/Horsebox%20Guide%20low%20res.pdf\" title=\"Download 'A guide for horsebox and trailer owners' (PDF, 2.2MB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘A guide for horsebox and trailer owners’ (PDF, 2.2MB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/annual-test-for-lorries-buses-and-trailers/book-your-test","slug":"book-your-test","order":2,"title":"Book your test","body":"<p>You can book up to 93 days ahead, using the online test booking system for either a <a href=\"/book-a-single-annual-test-online\" title=\"Book a single annual test online\">single test</a> or <a href=\"/book-tests-for-multiple-vehicles-online\" title=\"Book tests for multiple vehicles online\">multiple tests</a>. You must be already registered with <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> to use the multiple test booking service.</p>\n\n<p>Find your nearest test station and their contact details on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.transportoffice.gov.uk/crt/doitonline/bl/vosateststationlocations/vosateststationlocations.htm\" title=\"VOSA Testing Stations\"><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> website.</a></p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/annual-test-for-lorries-buses-and-trailers/fees","slug":"fees","order":3,"title":"Fees","body":"<p>Fees for the annual test vary depending on the size and type of your vehicle.</p>\n\n<p>The current annual test and re-test fees for goods vehicles and for public service vehicles are available from <abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.dft.gov.uk/vosa/repository/HGV%20fees%20poster%202012.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Current annual test and re-test fees for goods vehicles' form (PDF, 195KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Current annual test