 <a href=\"/vehicle-approval/individual-vehicle-approval\" title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\"><abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></a> are exactly the same. The only differences are:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you can use voluntary <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> if your vehicle has already been registered in the UK</li>\n  <li>you won&rsquo;t have the same rights as with standard <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr></li>\n  <li>you&rsquo;ll have to pay <abbr title=\"Value Added Tax\">VAT</abbr> on the fee</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Cost of the schemes</h2>\n\n<p>You have to <a href=\"inspection-fees\" title=\"Inspection fees\">pay a fee</a> for the Vehicle and Operator Services Agency (<abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr>) to inspect your vehicle. </p>\n\n<h2>How to apply</h2>\n\n<p>To get voluntary <abbr title=\"Individual Vehicle Approval\">IVA</abbr> for a passenger car or light goods vehicle (up to 3,500 kg), send a completed application to the address on the form. </p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_files/Application_for_VIVA_M1_N1_1.doc\" title=\"Download 'Application for voluntary (non statutory) Individual Vehicle Approval' (DOC, 709KB)\">Download ‘Application for voluntary (non statutory) Individual Vehicle Approval’ (DOC, 709KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Vehicle and Operator Services Agency\">VOSA</abbr> has produced guidance on completing the form.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.businesslink.gov.uk/Transport_files/VIVA_M1_N1_Guidance_Notes.pdf\" title=\"Download 'Guidance on completing voluntary Individual Vehicle Approval application form' (PDF, 60KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Guidance on completing voluntary Individual Vehicle Approval application form’ (PDF, 60KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Voluntary application for larger passenger cars